label: Hermetschwil, Benediktinerinnenkloster, Cod. membr. 35

metadata.label: Summary (English)
metadata.value: This book of hours of Savoyard or western Swiss origin, produced in about 1490, was originally the property of the Bern patrician Thomas Schöni and his wife Jeanne d'Arbignon. The miniatures were ascribed to the Meister of the breviary of Jost von Silenen.
